Past continuous and past simple
1.
1) Lucy broke her arm last week. It happened when she was painting her room. She fell off the ladder.
2) The train arrived at the station and Paula got off.
Two friends of hers, Joh and Rachel were waiting to meet her.
3) Yesterday Sue was walking along the road when she met James.
He was going to the station to catch a train and he was carrying a bag.
They stopped to talk for a few minutes.
2.
1) What was the weather like when you got up this morning? It was raining.
2) Was Jane busy whey you went to see her? Yes, she was studying.
3) Did Paul call you this morning? Yes, he called while I was having breakfast.
4) Was Tracey at work today? No, she didn't go to work. She was ill.
5) How fast were you driving when the police stopped you?
I'n not sure, but I wasn't driving very fast.
6) Did your team win the football match yesterday?
The weather was very bad, so we didn't play.
7) How did you break the window? We were playing football. I kicked the ball and it hit the window.
8) Did you see Jessica last night? Yes, she was wearing a very nice jacket.
9) What were you doing at 2 o'clock this morning? I was asleep.
10) I lost my keys last night. How did you get into your room?
I climbed in through a window.
3)
1) Sandra was cooking dinner when we came home.
2) I was going to work, when I met Natasha.
3) They weren't working. They were chatting.
4) I was working at 3 o'clock yesterday afternoon.
5) It wasn't raining because we had launch in the garden.
6) When I entered the room, Anna and Rodrigo were speaking Spanish.
7) I was very tired yesterday, so I went to bed at 9 o'clock.
8) When Sasha called Anna was watching TV.